eanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Atkin</i> (composed of <i>Ade</i> + the diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>). This is one of the many medieval pet forms of   Adam  . Compare Scottish   Aitken  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":49,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":58,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":69,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Anne Atkins was born about 1500, in Wiltshire, England, her father, Robert Atkins, was 26 and her mother, Unknown, was 21. She married John Timbrell in 1518. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died on 26 March 1574, in Featherstone, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 75."},"et":{"Abt. 1500–26 March 1574":"umbes 1500–26. märts 1574","1500–1574":"1500–1574","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1519–1604":"1519–1604","1519–1728":"1519–1728","1519–Male":"1519–Surnud","1519–Female":"1519–Surnud","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","after 1519":"pärast 1519","1560":"1560","1480":"1480","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","Abt. 1500":"umbes 1500","26 March 1574":"26. märts 1574","1475":"1475","1574":"1574","1519":"1519","1728":"1728","1518":"1518","1549":"1549","1604":"1604","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Preston, Gloucestershire, England":"Preston, Gloucestershire, England","Buried: Featherstone, Yorkshire, England":"Featherstone, Yorkshire, England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England","Preston on Stowe, Gloucester, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucester, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt. 1500–26 March 1574":"noin 1500–26. maaliskuuta 1574","1500–1574":"1500–1574","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1519–1604":"1519–1604","1519–1728":"1519–1728","1519–Male":"1519–Kuollut","1519–Female":"1519–Kuollut","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","after 